    <div class="image-text-container">
        <figure class="image-wrapper">
          <img
          src="/credentials/epa-certified-appliance-repair-company1.webp"
            alt="EPA Certified Appliance Repair Company"
            width="500"
            height="243"
          />
          <figcaption>EPA Certified Appliance Repair Company</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="text-content">
            <section>
                <h2>Trusted EPA-608 Certified Technicians for Safe & Reliable Appliance Repairs</h2>
                <p>When dealing with appliances that use refrigerants, such as <strong>refrigerators, freezers, air conditioners, and heat pumps</strong>, it's crucial to hire <strong>EPA-608 certified technicians</strong>. At <strong>Same Day Appliance Repair</strong>, we ensure that all our technicians are <strong>certified, trained, and compliant</strong> with EPA regulations for safe refrigerant handling and appliance repairs.</p>
                <p><a style="color:#000000" href="https://search.dca.ca.gov/details/3900/A/49573/951ad0b8d76082995aaae473100fe0a1" title="BBB Accredited Appliance Repair" target="_blank"><b>Click Here to see oficial information about EPA Certification</b></a>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>✅ Why Choose Our EPA-608 Certified Technicians?</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li> <strong>Certified for Safe Refrigerant Handling</strong> – Our technicians are <strong>EPA-608 certified</strong>, ensuring compliance with environmental laws.</li>
                    <li><strong>Same-Day Appliance Repairs</strong> – Get your appliances back in working order <strong>as quickly as possible</strong>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Expert Repairs for Refrigerant-Based Appliances</strong> – We specialize in fixing <strong>refrigerators, freezers, air conditioners, and heat pumps</strong>.</li>
                    <li> <strong>Environmentally Responsible Service</strong> – We follow <strong>EPA guidelines</strong> to ensure <strong>eco-friendly refrigerant disposal</strong>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Upfront Pricing & Warranty-Backed Repairs</strong> – No hidden fees! We provide <strong>transparent pricing</strong> and a <strong>service warranty</strong>.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
                </div></div>

                <section>
                    <h2>What is EPA-608 Certification?</h2>
                    <p>The <strong>EPA-608 certification</strong> is required by the <strong>U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)</strong> for technicians who work with refrigerants. This certification ensures that technicians are properly trained to <strong>prevent refrigerant leaks, recover and recycle refrigerants safely, and comply with all environmental regulations</strong>.</p>
                    <p>At <strong>Same Day Appliance Repair</strong>, we employ <strong>only EPA-608 certified professionals</strong> to guarantee <strong>safe and compliant appliance repairs</strong>.</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>Appliances We Repair with EPA-608 Certified Expertise</h2>
                    <div class="image-text-container">
                        <figure class="image-wrapper">
                          <img
                          src="/credentials/epa-certified-appliance-repair-company.webp"
                            alt="EPA Certified Appliance Repair Company"
                            width="500"
                            height="312"
                          />
                          <figcaption>EPA Certified Appliance Repair Company</figcaption>
                        </figure>
                        <div class="text-content">
                    <ul>
                        <li> <strong>Refrigerators & Freezers</strong> – Fixing <strong>compressor issues, refrigerant leaks, and cooling failures</strong>.</li>
                        <li><strong>Air Conditioners</strong> – Repairing <strong>low refrigerant levels, frozen coils, and poor cooling efficiency</strong>.</li>
                        <li></li> <strong>Heat Pumps</strong> – Fixing <strong>inefficient heating/cooling, refrigerant line leaks, and faulty compressors</strong>.</li>
                        <li><strong>Commercial Refrigeration Units</strong> – Handling <strong>walk-in freezers, display coolers, and industrial cooling systems</strong>.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Our <strong>EPA-608 certified technicians</strong> ensure that your appliance repair is done <strong>correctly, safely, and in compliance with federal regulations</strong>.</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>The Importance of Hiring an EPA-608 Certified Technician</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Compliance with Federal Environmental Laws</strong> – Protecting both your appliance and the environment.</li>
                        <li><strong>Safe & Legal Refrigerant Handling</strong> – Preventing harmful refrigerant leaks and ensuring proper recovery & disposal.</li>
                        <li><strong>Efficient & Long-Lasting Repairs</strong> – Ensuring that refrigerant-based appliances operate at <strong>peak performance</strong>.</li>
                        <li><strong>Peace of Mind</strong> – Knowing your appliance is in the hands of <strong>a certified and experienced professional</strong>.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <h2>📞 Schedule a Repair with Our EPA-608 Certified Technicians Today!</h2>
                    <p>If your refrigerator, air conditioner, or any other refrigerant-based appliance isn't working properly, don't take risks with unlicensed repairs. Contact <strong>Same Day Appliance Repair</strong> for <strong>safe, professional, and EPA-compliant appliance repair services</strong>.</p>
                </section>
